org.easybatch.core.api

Interface ComputationalRecordProcessor<I,O,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - The input object type.
    O - The output object type.
    R - The computed result type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    RecordProcessor<I,O>

    public interface ComputationalRecordProcessor<I,O,R>
extends RecordProcessor<I,O>
    A computational record processor is a processor that performs some computation on input records.
    The result of computation is returned at the end of batch execution. A computational record processor should be placed at the end of a pipeline.
    Author:
    Mahmoud Ben Hassine (mahmoud@benhassine.fr)
